title: Grateful Dead Live at Morgantown Civic Center on 1983-04-10
description: Samson & Delilah, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, My Brother Esau, Might As Well Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Add this to the collection The file quality is yummy.  The set lists are standard for this time period.  Highlights of the first set include a nice Rooster, luv the lethargic drummingI can picture Billy staring off into spacegreat stuff.  Tenn Jed is nice, I found myself fixated on the fart-like sounds coming from Phils bass.  The second set features a good Playin which floats off but does not quite make it to space.  This show is worth adding to your collection.  Enjoy!

nice group of songs... great sound quality nice fresh clean sounding show. worth downloading. early touch of grey is enjoyable some fumbles the lyric sync but nothing too bad. great uncle johns band>playin. predictable setlist but good sound quality makes up for it. go ahead and add it to your collection.
Predictable Setlist? Hilarious Comment. Good show.

Yea, no doubt Sampson & Delilah opener? that's sick. Iam a huge 83-84 fan and without Deadbase I can't think of any shows that Sampson opened up with. I know they did but its past rare. Its bloody in the middle. I know for a fact this is the only show in 84 that opened with Big Sampson. The rest of 1st set is not too out of the ordinary with the Western theme going on. As far as set 2, opening up with Touch into Women also rare may have done once or twice prior if that.(Wheres Dead Base when I need it)and on top of it again being 83-84 fan I can't think of any shows before and not too many after in this period of UJB>Playin> into Drums/Space>Wheel>Playin'>China Doll>Sugar Mag. Thats some sick stuff!!!

The Law Come To Get Ya'... Second Show Into A Grate Tour. Remember Well The West Virginia State Police Filing Into The Upper Right Side And Lining Up Riot Control Style. There Was A Huge Ripple In The Force And A Buzz From The Crowd But Most Were Unaware Until Jerry Emphatically Sang "Drink All Day Gonna Rock All Night... (Then Pointing To The Mountaineers State's Finest)...The Law Come To Get Ya' If Ya' Don't Walk Right. Well Ya' Know Children It's Like I Said,You Better Head Back To Tennessee Jed."Well The Crowd As One Turned Hissed And After A Minute Or Two Of Awkwardness,The Element Of Surprise Lost,They Slinked Out. Father Jubal Was Always Watching Out For Us. I Think Maybe He Still Is.Love You Always Jerry,Sail On.......
Seamless Show Very good show with Brent and jerry singing great . The drums segment was really solid and the second set just flew ! Unexpected favorite here

Dregs of this tour were still pretty good This and Hampton were the warmup shows for the real stuff to happen beginning two nights later.  This was probably the shortest show of this tour and has possibly the least interesting first set other than 4-13.  The second set doesn't start very well, either, although they played well enough to that point.  Uncle John's is where the show really kicks off, and the entire rest of the show smokes.  Even so, the rushed tempo means it all goes by very quickly; the good part of this is one tape side.  Still it was great hearing my first Uncle John's, Wheel, China Doll, and Sugar Mag (it was only my 3rd show), all performed very well.  Low 3 stars through Women, high 3 stars rest of show.

Sideway Set Up I see no mention that the band set up on the right side of the gym that night and played to the bleachers.  That is what made this show so special, but you had to be there to know.  The most intimate and small setting that I ever saw them.
